cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper focuses on developing and exploring deep anomaly detection techniques for image data using Capsule Networks. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as Capsule Networks are a relatively new and emerging area of deep learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as anomaly detection is a common problem in AI and Capsule Networks are a promising approach for this task. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as Capsule Networks are a type of neural network. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible as anomaly detection is also relevant in information retrieval and Capsule Networks have been applied in this area as well.
